{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "When I told you, in the mid-'30s, 1937, when those fascists, they came into the city.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And they had like a pogrom, where they would go to Jewish shuls.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And-- and they would beat up-- they would beat up people on the street.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they came to-- to the villages there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember, it was like a holiday like, Sukkos.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when they came to the next village, to Batarci, somebody from the Jewish in Batarci send over an emissary to Comlausa that the fascists are coming to my village.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remembered, we-- all the people from the shul went out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They went to the edge of the village, and they gathered stones.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made like-- they made like piles of stones.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were about maybe four or five students with bicycles.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, they came specially to beat up Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When they reached the edge of my village, we were waiting for them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We beat them up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They left the bicycles there, and they ran away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But of course, again, because in my village, people grew up plain, they grew up proud, they were not afraid-- I mean, of course, they were afraid.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But for a few fascists, they're not going to run.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when I think back-- and I remember that incident, I'm very proud that at least we stood up.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I believe that if the Jewish people in other places would have organized and stayed-- and, you know, to a certain extent-- not with the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I'm not talking about the Nazis because what the Nazis did, that was a plan.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You couldn't defeat Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "France couldn't defeat-- nah, I mean.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I'm talking local incidents, like pogroms and stuff like this-- we would've been-- we would've been OK.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then in 1939, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] if you-- you know, there is the-- what do you call the-- excuse me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can just say something else.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My village-- the first people to settle in my village, I think-- I think, as far as I could-- as-- but as far as I know, not remember-- as far as I know, must've been maybe in the mid-19th century, like 1840, around the 1840s.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How do I know this?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because I was born in Comlausa.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother was born in Comlausa.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My grandmother was born in Comlausa.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My grandmother's parents were born in Comlausa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's my great-grandfather and grandmother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "No, only my great-grandfather was born in Comlausa, not my great-grandmother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it goes like this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My name is Yankl.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother's name is Rifka.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My grandmother's name was Leah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My great-grandfather, who was born-- I'm talking only people who were born in Comlausa, his name was was Shloimo Leazar.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And his father-- his father's name was Mayer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they settled-- whether they were the first one or not-- this, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But as I say, I could trace it back almost to the mid-19th century.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This Mayer had three children.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One was Yankl, and one son's name was Lachida.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one son's name was Shloimo Leazar.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This Yankl, he's the one that my father inherited.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He-- because he was adopted to-- as I said before.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The ?] Lachida and Shloimo Leazar, they both had like 10, 12 children each.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So my whole village-- actually, my whole village, I would say 90% were related.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were cousins, uncles, all related.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In other words, all the 26 families, I would probably say anywhere, 21, maybe 21, 22 families were in a somes way related-- related.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was only a day away from Simchas Torah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Simchas Torah, everybody got drunk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whoever could give more wine on the table, when he started to drink, and he was elected president.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So most of the fights would begin then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Why it was he elected, why wasn't he elected, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And sometimes those fights were pretty rough.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember we used to have a gate around my shul, made out of, like a-- like a picket fence, and they would take apart a whole fence.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They-- they needed some clubs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But one thing I'll say, when they finished fighting, they all walked together like brothers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Outside, you never knew there was a fight.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Once, I remember there was a fight because somebody called my grandfather [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Ask me what [NON-ENGLISH] is.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This is something you say Passover by the-- by the seder.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But because they called him [NON-ENGLISH] was a good enough-- a good enough reason to have a fight.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So they were fighting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In a way, it was a way-- it's-- it was a way of letting off steam because it was a small village.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
